// @run
// @log 7
// @log 9
// @log 1
// @log 1
// @log 2
// if as an expression: true/false branches, comparison conditions, &&, and else if.
// The last line's literal `if false … else if true …` chain trips the
// constant-condition lint (an if-expression in a call argument is walked too):
// @warning This branch is never taken: its condition is always `false`
// @warning This branch is never taken: a preceding condition is always `true`
print(if 5 > 3 then 7 else 9)
print(if 2 > 5 then 7 else 9)
print(if 3 == 3 then 1 else 0)
print(if (5 > 3) && (2 > 1) then 1 else 0)
print(if false then 1 else if true then 2 else 3)
